      <sentence>
        <infon key="n">2</infon>
        <offset>116</offset>
        <text>Kelp forests worldwide are known as hotspots for macroscopic biodiversity and primary production, yet very little is known about the biodiversity and roles of microorganisms in these ecosystems.
</text>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
        <infon key="n">3</infon>
        <offset>311</offset>
        <text>Secondary production by heterotrophic bacteria associated to kelp is important in the food web as a link between kelp primary production and kelp forest consumers.
</text>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
        <infon key="n">4</infon>
        <offset>475</offset>
        <text>The aim of this study was to investigate the relationship between bacterial diversity and two important processes in this ecosystem; bacterial secondary production and primary succession on kelp surfaces.
</text>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
        <infon key="n">5</infon>
        <offset>680</offset>
        <text>To address this, kelp, Laminaria hyperborea, from southwestern Norway was sampled at different geographical locations and during an annual cycle.
</text>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
        <infon key="n">6</infon>
        <offset>826</offset>
        <text>Pyrosequencing (454-sequencing) of amplicons of the 16S rRNA gene of bacteria was used to study bacterial diversity.
</text>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
        <infon key="n">7</infon>
        <offset>943</offset>
        <text>Incorporation of tritiated thymidine was used as a measure of bacterial production.
</text>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
        <infon key="n">8</infon>
        <offset>1027</offset>
        <text>Our data show that bacterial diversity (richness and evenness) increases with the age of the kelp surface, which corresponds to the primary succession of its bacterial communities.
</text>
